<ext_description linkend="Swept_solid_arm">
</ext_description><!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Swept_solid_arm  Entity: Axis1_placement  
   <express_ref linkend="swept_solid:arm:Swept_solid_arm.Axis1_placement"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Swept_solid_arm.Axis1_placement">
        An <b>Axis1_placement</b> is a type of
        <express_ref linkend="swept_solid:arm:Swept_solid_arm.Detailed_geometric_model_element" />
        	that defines the position of a single axis in 3 dimensional space.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Swept_solid_arm  Entity: Axis1_placement  Attribute: axis 
   <express_ref linkend="swept_solid:arm:Swept_solid_arm.Axis1_placement.axis"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Swept_solid_arm.Axis1_placement.axis">
 the direction of the axis.</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Swept_solid_arm  Entity: Axis1_placement  Attribute: position 
   <express_ref linkend="swept_solid:arm:Swept_solid_arm.Axis1_placement.position"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Swept_solid_arm.Axis1_placement.position">
a reference point lying on the axis.</ext_description><!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Swept_solid_arm  Entity: Extruded_solid  
   <express_ref linkend="swept_solid:arm:Swept_solid_arm.Extruded_solid"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Swept_solid_arm.Extruded_solid">
        An <b>Extruded_solid</b> is a type of
        <express_ref linkend="swept_solid:arm:Swept_solid_arm.Swept_solid" />
formed by extruding the swept face along a straight line for a distance equal to the <b>depth</b>.

</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Swept_solid_arm  Entity: Extruded_solid  Attribute: depth 
   <express_ref linkend="swept_solid:arm:Swept_solid_arm.Extruded_solid.depth"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Swept_solid_arm.Extruded_solid.depth">
the distance the face is to be swept, this is also the length of all the new edges created by the extrusion operation.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Swept_solid_arm  Entity: Extruded_solid  Attribute: extruded_direction 
   <express_ref linkend="swept_solid:arm:Swept_solid_arm.Extruded_solid.extruded_direction"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Swept_solid_arm.Extruded_solid.extruded_direction">
the direction in which the face is swept to create the solid; this direction shall not be perpendicular to the face normal.
</ext_description><!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Swept_solid_arm  Entity: Solid_of_revolution  
   <express_ref linkend="swept_solid:arm:Swept_solid_arm.Solid_of_revolution"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Swept_solid_arm.Solid_of_revolution">
        A <b>Solid_of_revolution</b> is a type of
        <express_ref linkend="swept_solid:arm:Swept_solid_arm.Swept_solid" />
formed by revolving the swept planar face about an axis in the plane of the face. The axis shall not intersect 
the interior of the face.</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Swept_solid_arm  Entity: Solid_of_revolution  Attribute: angle 
   <express_ref linkend="swept_solid:arm:Swept_solid_arm.Solid_of_revolution.angle"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Swept_solid_arm.Solid_of_revolution.angle">
the angle through which the face is revolved to create the solid. This angle is measured from the plane of the <b> swept_face</b>.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Swept_solid_arm  Entity: Solid_of_revolution  Attribute: axis 
   <express_ref linkend="swept_solid:arm:Swept_solid_arm.Solid_of_revolution.axis"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Swept_solid_arm.Solid_of_revolution.axis">
the axis about which the face is revolved to generate the solid. The <b>axis</b> shall lie in the plane of the face.
</ext_description><!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Swept_solid_arm  Entity: Swept_solid  
   <express_ref linkend="swept_solid:arm:Swept_solid_arm.Swept_solid"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Swept_solid_arm.Swept_solid">
        A <b>Swept_solid</b> is a type of
        <express_ref linkend="swept_solid:arm:Swept_solid_arm.Detailed_geometric_model_element" />
that defines a solid produced by sweeping a face.
	 The face is based on a surface and is bounded by edges and vertices. The face is required to be a 
	 <b>face_surface</b> and may be an <b><express_ref linkend="topologically_bounded_surface:arm:Topologically_bounded_surface_arm.Advanced_face"/></b>.

        <p>The following constraints apply:</p>
<ul>
<li>The face is required to be fully bounded by edge loops;</li> 
<li>At most one of the bounds of the face may define the outer bound; </li>
<li> The surface geometry of the face is required to be a plane. </li>
<li>The only types of sweeping operation permitted are linear extrusion or simple rotation about an axis. </li>
<li> The geometry of all bounding edges of the face shall be fully defined as edge curves; </li>
<li>The types of curve used to define the geometry of edges of the swept face shall be restricted to lines, conics, polylines, surface curves, or b spline curves;</li>
<li>All vertices used in the face definition shall be of type vertex point with geometry defined by a cartesian point;</li>
<li>The use of oriented paths in the definition of the edge loops of the advanced face is prohibited;</li>
<li> If a polyline is used as part of a face bound, it shall contain at least three points;</li>
</ul> </ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Swept_solid_arm  Entity: Swept_solid  Attribute: swept_face 
   <express_ref linkend="swept_solid:arm:Swept_solid_arm.Swept_solid.swept_face"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Swept_solid_arm.Swept_solid.swept_face">
the face defining the area to be swept to create the solid. The <b>swept_face</b> may contain one or more holes.
</ext_description>
</ext_descriptions>
